The paper proposes a new logic for knowledge representation and automated reasoning in cognitive robots, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. The paper also mentions a Hilbert style axiomatization and inference rules, which are topics typically studied in the Logic (cs.LO) and Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of the proposed logic through constraint programming, which is a topic that falls under the Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
